---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site.mjs';
---
<Base title="Our story" description="The story behind Tantu Kala — handmade crochet, one knot at a time.">
  <div class="wrap py-10 max-w-2xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl">Our story</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-saffron font-semibold">Tantu Kala — "the art of thread"</p>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-ink/80 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Tantu Kala began at a kitchen table, with a ball of cotton yarn and a hook.
        <em>[Replace this with your real story — where it started, who makes the pieces,
        why crochet. Handmade buyers connect with the maker as much as the make.]</em>
      </p>
      <p>
        Every rakhi is crocheted by hand, one knot at a time. That means no two are
        identical — small variations aren't flaws, they're the fingerprint of something
        made by a person, for a person.
      </p>
      <p>
        This Raksha Bandhan, we're making a limited number of rakhis. When a design says
        "made to order," it's being crocheted especially for you — so it takes a few days,
        and it's worth the wait.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 card p-6 bg-sand">
      <p class="font-display text-xl text-maroon">Made by hand · Made in India</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink/70">
        Have a custom request or a bulk order? Message us on
        <a href={`https://wa.me/${SITE.whatsapp}`} class="text-henna font-semibold underline">WhatsApp</a>
        or <a href={SITE.instagram} class="text-henna font-semibold underline">Instagram</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <a href="/" class="btn-primary mt-8">Shop this season's rakhis</a>
  </div>
</Base>
